<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Personally, I think neither Stun nor Mez should work the way they do in RvR, I agree that both of them are just so dang overpowering.<P>My thoughts are that they tone down both Mez and Stun, and they REIMBURSE the classes affected with it (specifically those built around it, such as Sorcerers, Healers, and Bards, I don't think any class is built around Stun) with something that's equally useful in RvR.  People say "You guys still have pets, DoTs, debuffs, you guys are fine."<P>Our pets are little threat, which are weaker than the normal mob once they're charmed and will simply walk away if we die.<P>DoTs are rare, guzzle power, and don't stack with other peoples' DoTs.<P>Debuffs don't work effectively or noticably in RvR.<P>So while I agree that Mez and Stun need to be seriously toned down, I will never agree with a patch which does so without reimbursing those classes which it cripples.
</FONT>
