"Lets try to brainstorm some new spell ideas. "<P>The idea behind brainstorming is to get feedback on the pros and cons of each new spell idea.  If you just want spell ideas with no feedback to them at all, it is pretty pointless.  We could just throw out spells that would make us super-uber.   Everyone has an opinion, but you may not have thought about it from all angles.  Providing constructive feedback is positive.  For example:<P>We need a stun spell.<P>Constructive response:  Stun is overpowering.  We need less classes with stun, not more.  Being able to stop someone cold and continue to nuke them while they are helpless is not something sorcerers need.<P>Non-Constructive: U R D suq.  Stun = n00b<P><BR>That being said...<P>Body:  Leave be<BR>Body Spec: Leave be<P>Mind: Leave be<BR>Mind Spec:  AOE Confuse<P>Matter: Leave be<BR>Matter Spec: DoT stacks with non-spec line<BR>Add new spell: Reverse gravity - AoE, 1500 range<P>Level 8:  10 feet, 10% damage, Cost: 10%<BR>Level 16: 20 feet, 15% damage, Cost: 15%<BR>Level 24: 30 feet, 20% damage, Cost: 20%<BR>Level 32: 40 feet, 25% damage, Cost: 25%<BR>Level 40: 50 feet, 30% damage, Cost: 30%<BR>Level 48: 60 feet, 35% damage, Cost: 35%<P>--------------------<P>Malachai Mindbender<BR>Sorcerer of Avalon<BR>Guinivere
